b'Qualifications'
b' Ph.D. Electrical Engineering and Computer Science University of Illinois at Chicago, Illinois'
b' Laurea of Doctor in Electronics Engineering, summa cum laude Politecnico di Milano, Milan, Italy'
b'Professional Achievements'
b' Fellow, IEEE, 2016'
b' Chair, IEEE Antennas and Propagation Society Distinguished Lecturer Program, 2015-present'
b'IEEE Antennas and Propagation Society Distinguished Lecturer Program, 2015-present'
b' General Chairman, 2012 IEEE International Symposium on Antennas and Propagation and USNC-URSI National Radio Science Meeting, Chicago, IL, July 8-14, 2012'
b'2012 IEEE International Symposium on Antennas and Propagation and USNC-URSI National Radio Science Meeting,'
b' Vice-General Chairman, 2008 URSI General Assembly'
b'2008 URSI General Assembly'
b' Member at Large, USNC-URSI, 2012-2017'
b'USNC-URSI,'
b' Elected, Administrative Committee Member, IEEE Antennas and Propagation Society, 2012-2014'
b' Chair, IEEE Chicago Chapter of the Antennas and Propagation/Microwave Theory and Techniques Societies, 2011-present'
b' Chair, USNC-URSI Student Paper Competition and Travel Award, 2009-2014'
b' Chair, USNC-URSI Commission E \xe2\x80\x93 Electromagnetic Environment and Interference, 2009-2011'
b' Associate Editor, Radio Science, 2014-present'
b'Radio Science,'
b' Associate Editor, IEEE Transactions on Antennas and Propagation, 2013-present'
b'IEEE Transactions on Antennas and Propagation,'
b' Associate Editor, IEEE Antennas and Wireless Propagation Letters, 2002-2014'
b' Guest Editor, Radio Science, Special Section on the National Radio Science Meeting, 2012'
b' Lead Guest Editor, International Journal of Antennas and Propagation, 2012'
b' Guest Editor, Electromagnetics Journal, Special Issue, Dec. 2005 and Jan. 2006'
b' UIC Teaching Recognition Program, 2013'
b' College of Engineering Faculty Undergraduate Advising Award, 2008, 2013'
b' UIC Areas of Excellence Program Award Recipient, 2012'
b' College of Engineering Faculty Research Award, 2008'
b' College of Engineering Gold Faculty Research Award, 2006'
b' Air Force Summer Faculty Fellow, 2009'
b'Research Interests'
b' Radar Systems: Ground penetrating radar, Radio Frequency Tomography, Propagation models of the electromagnetic field in complex environments, Inversion methods for inverse scattering problems, Multipath effects'
b' Antenna design: Vector antennas for direction of arrival applications and/or improved communication channel capacity'
b' Computation of special functions: Maliuzhinets functions, Mathieu functions, Oblate and prolate spheroidal functions'
b' Electromagnetic scattering: High-frequency methods: Physical Optics, Geometrical Theory of Diffraction, Uniform Theory of Diffraction, Incremental Theory of Diffraction; Analytical solutions of canonical scattering problems'
b' Electromagnetic measurements: Measurement of antenna properties, Measurements to validate electromagnetic scattering theories'
b' Electromagnetic Compatibility: Interaction of high-power ultrawideband electromagnetic pulses (HEMP) with digital systems, Electromagnetic shielding, Penetration of electromagnetic fields into cavities'
b' Wireless Communications: Methods for the propagation of the electromagnetic field in complex environments, ray tracing.'
b' Magnetic Resonance Imaging: Fast computation of the distribution of the radiofrequency field (B1+) in ultra-high MRI applications, Fast computation of temperature effects due to the radiofrequency field (B1+)'
b'Research Projects'
b' MURI on the Effects of High Power Electromagnetic Waves on Digital Systems (HPEM, HEMP)'
b'MURI on the Effects of High Power Electromagnetic Waves on Digital Systems'
b' MURI on Adaptive waveform design'
b'MURI on Adaptive waveform design'
b' Darpa project on Detection in Complex Maritime Environments'
